#: Game
msgid "[Main game intro]"
msgstr ""
"# Game Over or QED? \n"
"\n"
"Are you curious what computer-assisted theorem proving feels like compared to pen-and-paper "
"mathematics? Then you've come to the right place! In this game, you will learn how to work "
"with the proof assistant Lean 4 and the proof library mathlib.\n"
"You will verify sum formulas by induction, show that a mapping is surjective if and only if "
"it has a right inverse, prove that there are uncountably many sequences of natural numbers, "
"and characterise the trace as a map among all functions defined on the space of square "
"matrices.\n"
"\n"
"The interface is somewhat simplified, but if you activate *editor mode*, it feels almost "
"like VSCode, the standard IDE for Lean.\n"
"On a smartphone or tablet, it is better to stay in the default *typewriter mode* and turn "
"off all autocompletion/autocorrection features of your on-screen keyboard (a.k.a. \"smart "
"typing\", \"text recognition\", \"predictive text\" etc.). \n"
"\n"
"Click on the first planet *Logo* to start your journey.\n"
"\n"
"## Progress\n"
"\n"
"Your game progress is stored locally in your browser as *site data*. You can also download "
"your progress via the menu and save it to your disk. Note that many browsers delete *site "
"data* and *cookies* together. \n"
"\n"
"## Rules \n"
"\n"
"If you want to take the game seriously, keep the default setting *Rules: regular*.\n"
"If you just want to poke around, select *Rules: relaxed*.  This will allow you to access "
"every level immediately, even if you haven't solved the previous levels yet.\n"
"\n"
"## News \n"
"\n"
"`[2026-03-28]` The game is now available in English! \n"
"\n"
"For background information and credits, see *Game Info* in the menu."

